our mass communications media to share serious ideas. Since television images replace the written word, Postman argues that television confounds serious issues by demeaning and undermining political discourse and by turning real, complex issues into superficial images, less about ideas and thoughts and more about entertainment. He also argues that television is not an effective way of providing education, as it provides only top-down information transfer, rather than the interaction that he believes is necessary to maximize learning. He refers to the relationship between information and human response as the Information-action ratio.","isGrAuthor":false,"works":{"__typename":"ContributorWorksConnection","totalCount":33},"profileImageUrl":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/authors/1193415026i/41963.jpg","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/41963.Neil_Postman","user":null,"viewerIsFollowing":null,"followers":{"__typename":"ContributorFollowersConnection","totalCount":656}},"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.XnWNc0P87M91YsET_pgwUA":{"id":"kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.XnWNc0P87M91YsET_pgwUA","__typename":"Contributor","name":"Andrew Postman","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/671055.Andrew_Postman","isGrAuthor":false},"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.QcO042nAQCirV1fLUcYR-g":{"id":"kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.QcO042nAQCirV1fLUcYR-g","__typename":"Book","legacyId":74034,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/74034.Amusing_Ourselves_to_Death","title":"Amusing Ourselves to Death: Public Discourse in the Age of Show Business","titleComplete":"Amusing Ourselves to Death: Public Discourse in the Age of Show Business","description":"Television has conditioned us to tolerate visually entertaining material measured out in spoonfuls of time, to the detriment of rational public discourse and reasoned public affairs. In this eloquent, persuasive book, Neil Postman alerts us to the real and present dangers of 